    - The various titles throughout his career (閤門祗候, 御史, 侍郞, etc.) reflect the complex bureaucratic hierarchy of the Goryeo dynasty. Each promotion marked significant advancement in the official system.
    - Unmun Mountain (雲門山) was likely a strategic military location where resistance to the rebels was organized.
    - The epitaph's final verses follow the traditional form of commemorative poetry, emphasizing the deceased's virtue continuing through his descendants and reputation.
